Speaker 2: Who do I have the pleasure of speaking with today?

Speaker 1: Okay, yeah, I can look into this.

Speaker 2: Yeah, can you just cancel the subscription?

Speaker 1: Okay, what is your date of birth?

Speaker 2: September 17, 64.

Speaker 2: Okay, great.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so if you don't want to receive regular refills with your prescription, you certainly don't have to.

Speaker 2: You always have the option with your prescription to place it on hold for up to six months at a time,

Speaker 1: just because six months is when the prescription would expire.

Speaker 2: If we didn't refill it, and the way that would work is you could still order before the end of July, six months from now.

Speaker 1: You just have to give us a call to place the order yourself whenever you are ready to order.

Speaker 2: So what I got to do now, because I'm trying to log back in,

Speaker 1: and I couldn't log in.

Speaker 2: Oh, weird.

Speaker 1: Yeah, yeah, it's weird.

Speaker 2: I can see if they can send you another login,

Speaker 1: but I can just place your prescription on hold,

Speaker 2: and then whenever you are ready to order,

Speaker 1: if it is before the end of July or July 27th,

Speaker 2: just give us a call to place it yourself,

Speaker 1: and I'll see if they can send you a login.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 2: Thanks, Connie.

Speaker 1: Yeah, have a good day.
